Experiment No.—8 : Group By and Having Clause 
 
For Tables:  
Students(name, age, email, phone_no, category) 
Enrollments(enroll_id, Student_id, course_id, enroll_date) 
course_details(cname, duration, FEES_DETAILS) 
a) Write a query to find the total number of students in each category from the Students 
table. 
b) Write a query to find the number of students in each age group from the Students 
table. 
c) Display categories having more than 3 students 
d) Find courses having more than 5 enrollments

a

SELECT category,
COUNT(*) AS Total_Students
FROM students
GROUP BY category;

b

SELECT age,
COUNT(*) AS Total_Students
FROM students
GROUP BY age;

c

SELECT category,
COUNT(*) AS Total_Students
FROM students
GROUP BY category
HAVING COUNT(*) > 3;

d

SELECT course_id,
COUNT(student_id) AS Total_Enrollments
FROM enrollments_new
GROUP BY course_id
HAVING COUNT(student_id) > 5;
